[{"id":"VR038241","type":"mcq","stimulusHtml":"<p class=\"stem_paragraph\">Figure 1 shows the inheritance of a particular genetic condition in three generations of one family. Which of the following best explains the observed pattern of inheritance?</p>\n","rubricRef":"VR038241_rubric","features":[{"type":"sharedpassage","html":"<div>\n<div class=\"stimulus_reference\">\n<div class=\"passage\">\n<div class=\"prose style:1\">\n<div class=\"standalone_image\" style=\"margin-left: 40px;\">&nbsp;</div>\n\n<div class=\"standalone_image\"><img alt=\"The figure presents a pedigree with three generations. The first generation has an unaffected male and an affected female. The second generation offspring are two affected males and two affected females in alternating order. Each of the second generation affected offspring is paired with an unaffected mate. In the third generation, an affected male and unaffected female produce an unaffected male and unaffected female; an affected female and unaffected male produce an affected male and an affected female; an affected male and unaffected female produce an unaffected female and an unaffected male; and an affected female and an unaffected male produce an affected female and an affected male.Â \" height=\"337\" src=\"https://assets.learnosity.com/organisations/537/VR038241.g02.png\" width=\"350\" /></div>\n</div>\n</div>\n\n<p class=\"standalone_statement style:1\">Figure 1. A pedigree of three generations of a family that have a high frequency of a particular genetic condition</p>\n</div>\n</div>\n"}],"choicesHtml":["<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">The condition is passed randomly because of the independent assortment of chromosomes.</p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">The condition is passed from fathers to sons via a <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"Y\" role=\"math\"><math alttext=\"Y\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mtext>Y</mtext></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span>-linked gene.</p>\n","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">The condition is passed from mothers to sons via an <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"X\" role=\"math\"><math alttext=\"X\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mtext>X</mtext></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span>-linked gene.</p>\n","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">The condition is passed from mothers to offspring via a mitochondrial gene.</p>\n"],"answer":3}]